          <div class="col-md-6 col-sm-6 poems">
            <h3>Lost #8</h3>
            <p>The sun is sinking under the waves,
              Casting purples and pinks across the horizon,
              And you’re laughing – sincerely & joyful –
              This is where I realize I’ve missed the music of your laugh.

              Simon says it’s natural to grow apart from friends.
              I tell him that this is not natural.
              This is sawing off your right hand,
              Very slowly,
              With no anaesthetic,
              but never quite believing it’s gone.
            </p>

             <h3>Found #4</h3>
            <p>I proposed to her in the record shop near Satay bar.
              I made them play ‘In a Sentimental Mood’,
              And we danced in the scent of dust and age.
            </p>
